topLevelComment.text:
If anybody else is running into a deprecated bodyParser warning, this is what got rid of the command line error for me: 
mongoose.connect(`mongodb://${user}:${password}@${server}/${database}`, 
{ useNewUrlParser: true });

To clear depreciation warnings make mongoose.connect look like this:

mongoose.connect(`mongodb://${user}:${password}@${server}/${database}`, {
  useNewUrlParser: true,
  useCreateIndex: true,
})
